  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Healthy Practices, Strong Communities Program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the five-year Healthy Practices, Strong Communities (HPSC) program, Mercy Corps is working with communities in 10 sub-counties of Kitgum, Pader and Kaabong districts. Through addressing challenges to availability, access and utilization, the program is taking a broad and integrated approach to food security, appropriate to the specific needs of Uganda.  Over the life of the program, an estimated 105,000 people will directly benefit and 412,750 people will indirectly benefit from program activities, which are implemented under the following objectives (1) improved food production, consumption and sales among smallholder farming households; (2) improved health and nutrition among pregnant/ lactating women and children under five; and (3) sustainable safe water access and improved water, sanitation and hygiene practices.</narrative>
  </description>
